  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Statement.}\n\nThe secondary spectral function at the Trawin Zero Point encodes the distribution of excitations across the frequency domain.\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\n\nLet $\\Phi(t)$ be a temporal bridge function describing oscillatory behaviour near the TZP.\nThe secondary spectrum is defined as the modulus squared of its Fourier transform:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nS(\\omega) = \\left| \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} \\Phi(t) e^{-i\\omega t} \\, \\mathrm{d}t \\right|^2 .\n\\end{equation}\n\nThis quantity measures how strongly each frequency component contributes to the bridge dynamics.\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\n\nBy squaring the Fourier amplitude, the spectral function highlights resonant frequencies and suppresses phases, providing a power distribution over $\\omega$.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
